The paper deals with measuring and inducing abstract reasoning in neural networks, which is a topic that falls under the broad category of artificial intelligence (cs.AI). The paper also discusses the performance of popular models such as ResNets, which are commonly used in computer vision (cs.CV) and deep learning (cs.LG) research. The dataset and challenge proposed in the paper are designed to probe abstract reasoning, which is a topic that can also be relevant to natural language processing (cs.CL). Finally, the paper discusses the structure of a novel architecture designed to encourage reasoning, which falls under the category of neural networks (cs.NE).
